		<td><b>SnowBro's tools and song data</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Thought this may be of interest here.  Kent Hansen (SnowBro) recently posted a video on YouTube on how he creates NES music:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k4usxbg17Wg">http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=k4usxbg17Wg</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />The gist of it is he uses FastTracker 2 and converts them to an NES ROM/NSF with a custom tool, xm2nes (XM to NES).
<br />
<br />He also posted the source code to his tools and song data.  There's a 6502 assembler and linker, XORcyst, in one repository:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://repo.or.cz/w/xorcyst.git">http://repo.or.cz/w/xorcyst.git</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />The code to xm2nes along with a bunch of songs (in XM format), including those used in D-Pad Hero, is in another repo:
<br />
<br /><!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://repo.or.cz/w/kents-nes-stuff.git">http://repo.or.cz/w/kents-nes-stuff.git</a><!-- m -->
<br />
<br />-Dave

		

